Cinderella and Prince Charming were solving puzzles together in the palace garden. Prince gave her a challenge with numbers written on flower petals. He asked her to find whether any two petals (numbers in the array) add up to a given magical number. Can you help Cinderella write a program to solve this puzzle?

Input Format

The first line of input consists of an integer n, representing the size of the array.

The second line consists of n space-separated integers, representing the array elements.

The third line consists of an integer target, representing the required sum.

Constraints

NA

Output Format

If such a pair exists, print the indices of the two elements (0-based indexing).

If no pair exists, print -1 -1.

Sample Input 0

5
2 7 11 15 3
9
Sample Output 0

0 1
Explanation 0

Here, arr[0] + arr[1] = 2 + 7 = 9. Hence indices 0 1 are printed.

Sample Input 1

4
1 2 4 6
10
Sample Output 1

2 3
Explanation 1

Here, arr[2] + arr[3] = 4 + 6 = 10. Hence indices 2 3 are printed.


import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
      Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
      int n=sc.nextInt();
      int arr[]=new int[n];
      for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
      {
        arr[i]=sc.nextInt();
      }
      int k=sc.nextInt();
      int sum=0;
      for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++)
      {
        sum=arr[i]+arr[i+1];
        if(k==sum){
      System.out.print(i+" "+(i+1));
      return;}
      }
      System.out.print("-1");
    }
}
